Description: A set of tools for analyzing and modeling data subject to
    sampling biases. Provides functions to estimate the density and
    cumulative distribution functions from biased samples of continuous
    distributions. Includes the estimators proposed by Bhattacharyya et
    al. (1988) and Jones (1991) for density, and by Cox (2005) and Bose
    and Dutta (2022) for distribution, with different bandwidth selectors.
    Also includes a real length-biased dataset on shrub width from Muttlak
    (1988).
